      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@rebroad mapAlreadyAskedFor is what prevents asking additional peers for the same tx before it meets the AlreadyHave criteria. AlreadyHave doesn't currently return true if the tx is not an orphan but is rejected from the mempool; so as it stands, rejected tx must not be removed from the map since they are never included in AlreadyHave. #4542 would make this PR work.\n",
